## Nano-App Collection — Flavor-Specific Notes

### Architecture

Dashboard of independent micro-apps sharing a core framework. Zero dependencies, works on `file://`.

### Key Files

- `app_registry.js` — Single source of truth for all apps
- `core.js` — Shared framework (IIFE, instance isolation, namespaced state, theme)
- `index.html` — Dashboard that renders app grid from registry

### Adding a New App

1. Create `my-app/` directory with `index.html` + `app.js`
2. Use `Core.init('my-app')` for state management
3. Add entry to `app_registry.js`

See `.github/skills/nano-app-protocol/SKILL.md` for full checklist.

### Conventions

- All state through `State.save/load` — never raw `localStorage`
- No `fetch()` — use script-injection for `file://` compatibility
- Each app is self-contained and independently understandable
- Per-tab isolation via `sessionStorage` + `?instanceId=`
